The paper proposes a novel learning framework based on particle swarms for structure selection of polynomial nonlinear auto-regressive with exogenous inputs (NARX) models. This involves incorporating information about the cardinality (i.e., the number of terms) into the structure selection process. This work is related to machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) as it involves developing a new learning framework. It is also related to systems and control (SY) as it deals with modeling nonlinear systems. Additionally, it involves optimization and search algorithms, which are related to neural and evolutionary computing (NE) and social and information networks (SI). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE, and cs.SI.
